def remove_outlier_IQR(df):
    Q1=df.quantile(0.25)
    Q3=df.quantile(0.75)
    IQR=Q3-Q1
    df_final=df[~((df<(Q1-1.5*IQR)) | (df>(Q3+1.5*IQR)))]
    return df_final

Chi Squared Test (2)¶

H0 (null hypothesis): There is no association between Room Type and Neighbourhood Group.

H1 (alternate hypothesis): There is an association between Room Type and Neighbourhood Group.

In [221]:
tab = pd.crosstab(df['room_type'],df['neighbourhood_group'])
In [222]:
st.chi2_contingency(tab)
Out[222]:

The p value obtained (2.899e-23) is less than alpha (0.05) and thus the null hypothesis is rejected.

In [ ]:
def reg_report(true, pred, name='Test'):
    print("\n{} Results :\n".format(name))
    print("RSS is :",sum((pred-true)**2))
    print("RSE is :",math.sqrt(sum((pred-true)**2)*(1/(len(pred)-2))))
    print("TSS is :",sum((true-true.mean())**2))
    print("R Squared is :",1-(sum((pred-true)**2)/sum((true-true.mean())**2)))
    print("MSE is :",((pred-true)**2).mean())
    print('MAE is :',(abs(pred-true)).mean())
    
    

def eval_report(y_train, pred_train,y_test, pred_test):
    reg_report(y_train, pred_train, name='Train')
    reg_report(y_test, pred_test, name='Test')

Levene Test (for testing of variance) (4)¶

H0 (null hypothesis): variance(private_room) = variance(shared_room) = variance(entire_home)

H1 (alternate hypothesis): variance(private_room) != variance(shared_room) != variance(entire_home)

In [256]:
